<h4>
    Answers:
</h4>

<ol>
    <li>
        \( I = \frac{V}{R} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        \( R = \frac{V}{I} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        Voltage in terms of current and resistance.
    </li>
    <li>
        \( I = \frac{P}{V} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        \( V = \frac{P}{I} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        Power in terms of current and voltage.
    </li>
    <li>
        \( P = I^2 R \)
    </li>
    <li>
        \( P = \frac{V^2}{R} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        \( V= \sqrt{PR} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        \( I = \sqrt{\frac{P}{R}} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        \( R = \frac{P}{I^2} \)
    </li>
    <li>
        \( R = \frac{V^2}{P} \)
    </li>
</ol>
